The paper discusses the design of algorithms to optimize various aspects of crowdsourcing markets, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also focuses on the challenges of online decision making, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the strategic behavior of workers, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms that learn over time, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper touches on the modeling issues that inhibit theoretical research, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
